rest_of_day_open: I am looking forward to having a productive, yet peaceful, week. I am off work for the next two days and I have no real plans for the weekend, even though it is a holiday. I am happy about that, though, because it means I can do whatever I please!
critical_positive: My partner and I had a lot in common. Not just in shared experiences (which we had in scary levels of parallel), but also in our attitude and manner of speaking. We had experiences to share, and although there was a slight generation gap, it was not an impingment upon shared understanding
critical_negative: We are both clearly people who want to take center stage so we both had a problem with "waiting to talk" instead of actually listening to each other. We stumbled over each other's words a lot, talking over each other as we were racing to share experiences and thoughts with each other.

rest_of_day_open: I have many organizational tasks waiting to be completed, and with the Holiday coming up, they may be difficult to complete in a timely manner, so I'll do the best I can, and finish up what didn't get done next week. I hope to find a way to spend some quality time with my wife over the Holiday, even though external entertainment options are obviously pretty limited at the moment.
critical_positive: Marie and I come from very different backgrounds, and yet have much in common, so it was easy to share with each other. I enjoyed her enthusiasm and sense of humor. I found it easy enough both to listen to and talk to her. She seemed attentive, and I got the impression that she was enjoying the conversation, as I was.
critical_negative: I actually found that most aspects of our conversation worked pretty well, so nothing really sticks out in my mind as being difficult or clumsy. Marie has an outgoing personality, and I tend to get along well that kind of person for the most part. I wasn't entirely sure how she felt about the difference in our ages, however.
